                           Some paleographic features:
                           ሎ has the loop marking the 7th order attached directly to the body of the letter, without the linking line (cp. Äthiopische PaläographieÄthiopistische ForschungenSiegbertUhligStuttgartFranz Steiner Verlag GmbH1988Äthiopistische Forschungen2222CodicologyEthiopicPalaeographybm:Uhlig1988PalaographieCodicologyEthiopicPalaeographybm:Uhlig1988Palaographie242);
                           the bodies of some letters, e.g. ጰ, have a triangular or trapezoidal shape (cp. Äthiopische PaläographieÄthiopistische ForschungenSiegbertUhligStuttgartFranz Steiner Verlag GmbH1988Äthiopistische Forschungen2222CodicologyEthiopicPalaeographybm:Uhlig1988PalaographieCodicologyEthiopicPalaeographybm:Uhlig1988Palaographie191);
                           the stroke of some letters, e.g. ቀ, ዘ, are slanted to the left;
                           numerals are written without dashes (cp. Äthiopische PaläographieÄthiopistische ForschungenSiegbertUhligStuttgartFranz Steiner Verlag GmbH1988Äthiopistische Forschungen2222CodicologyEthiopicPalaeographybm:Uhlig1988PalaographieCodicologyEthiopicPalaeographybm:Uhlig1988Palaographie242);
                           ፪ has angular and not separated loops;
                           ፮ has the loop open, looking like "compressed" ፯;
                           ፴ has no left stroke.
                           እግዜኣብሔር፡ is often written with ኣ in the 4th order;
                           the crux ansata is seldom used (e.g.,  in black ink,  in red ink).


